<body>
<p>The emergence and contestation of theory groups is a fascinating topic at the heart of the philosophy of science. In “Conflict, Incommensurability, and Theory Groups: A Longitudinal Investigation of Citations in the Organization-Environment Literature,” David Roelfs develops a compelling article that explores how conflict among theory groups impacts theory group development and trajectory. David’s findings are certain to generate much thought, discussion, and debate.</p>
